==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corody
<hw>Cor"o*dy</hw> <pr>(k?r"?-d?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>corrodium</ets>, <ets>corredium</ets>, <ets>conredium</ets>,
furniture, provision: cf. OF. <ets>conroi</ets>. <ets>See</ets>
<er>Curry</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Law)</fld> <def>An allowance of meat,
drink, or clothing due from an abbey or other religious house for the
sustenance of such of the king's servants as he may designate to receive
it.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>corrody</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corol</ent>⟦br⟧
